                            {
                                "titre": "#### Materials Needed:",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "1. **Spoon** - 1 (preferably stainless steel)",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "2. **Fork** - 1 (preferably stainless steel)",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "3. **Magnet** - 1 (small, strong magnet such as a neodymium magnet)",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "4. **Epoxy Glue or Super Glue**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "5. **Pliers** - 2 pairs (one for holding, one for bending)",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "6. **Sandpaper or Metal File** - for smoothing edges",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "7. **Ruler** - for measuring",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "8. **Marker** - for marking bending points",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "#### Steps:",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "1. **Preparation:**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Clean the spoon and fork thoroughly to remove any grease or dirt.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Gather all materials and tools on a flat work surface.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "2. **Marking Bend Points:**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Use a ruler and marker to mark the bending points on the spoon and fork.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- On the spoon, mark about 1 inch from the bowl (this will be the base that supports the stand).",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- On the fork, mark the bending point about 2 inches from the prongs (this will form the holder for the razor).",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "3. **Bending the Spoon:**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Using the pliers, carefully bend the spoon at the marked point to a 90-degree angle. The handle should be bent upwards, forming the stand's base.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "4. **Bending the Fork:**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Use pliers to bend the fork at the marked point to a 90-degree angle.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Further bend the fork handle into a slight curve to create a cradle shape that will hold the razor.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- If needed, use the second pair of pliers to refine the bends and shape.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "5. **Smoothing Edges:**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Use sandpaper or a metal file to smooth any rough edges or sharp points on the spoon and fork to prevent injury and for a cleaner look.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "6. **Attaching the Fork to the Spoon:**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Position the fork's prongs so they will face upwards when attached to the spoon.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Apply epoxy glue or super glue to the contact point where the fork and spoon will be joined.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Firmly press the fork and spoon together and hold for a few minutes to ensure the glue sets. Allow the glue to cure completely as per the glue manufacturer's instructions.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "7. **Adding the Magnet:**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Decide on the best position for the magnet, typically at the base of the spoon, to keep the stand stable on a metallic surface.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Apply a small amount of epoxy or super glue to one side of the magnet and attach it to the base of the spoon.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Ensure the magnet is securely attached and allow the glue to cure completely.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "8. **Final Touches:**",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Check the stability of the stand and make any necessary adjustments to the bends and shapes of the spoon and fork.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Clean any excess glue and polish the stand for a finished look.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "#### Tips:",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- If the spoon or fork is difficult to bend, consider heating them slightly with a torch to make the metal more pliable (use caution and proper safety gear).",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "- Ensure the magnet is strong enough to hold the stand firmly in place but not so strong that it makes moving the stand difficult.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            },
                            {
                                "titre": "Your custom razor stand is now ready to use! The spoon provides a sturdy base, the fork holds the razor, and the magnet ensures it stays in place on metallic surfaces.",
                                "sous_etapes": []
                            }
